title: The City at World's End
creator: Edmond Hamilton
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The City at World's End, by Edmond Hamilton. Read by Mark Nelson. A surprise nuclear war may cause the End of the World, but not the way anyone could have imagined. A classic science fiction tale from Galaxy Magazine. (Summary by Mark Nelson) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; adventure; fantasy; fiction; science fiction

reviews.reviewbody:
A nuclear explosion sends a city forward in time, when the earth is dying due to the core having cooled off.  The people manage to find an abandoned city where they can warm themselves while they try to find others who can help them.  Unfortunately, those others just intend for them to be evacuated from their home planet.  

Further complicating things is the fact that those futuristic people just view them as dumb savages, no smarter than pets.  How can they overcome that prejudiced and save their home at the same time?

Excellent reading also, thanks!
